    "Penjelasan Kode:\n",
    "Manual Tuning:\n",
    "Untuk KMeans: Uji beberapa nilai n_clusters dan pilih konfigurasi dengan nilai silhouette score tertinggi.\n",
    "Untuk DBSCAN: Uji berbagai kombinasi eps dan min_samples dengan cara yang sama.\n",
    "Silhouette Score:\n",
    "Dihitung hanya jika terdapat lebih dari 1 kluster. Noise dalam DBSCAN tidak dimasukkan ke dalam perhitungan.\n",
    "Hasil:\n",
    "Menampilkan parameter terbaik untuk setiap model.\n",
    "Menyimpan hasil klusterisasi ke file CSV."

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans, DBSCAN\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load data\n",
    "data = pd.read_csv('DATA (1).csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop non-numeric columns if necessary\n",
    "numeric_data = data.select_dtypes(include=['number'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardize the data\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(numeric_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Hyperparameter tuning for KMeans\n",
    "kmeans_results = []\n",
    "for n_clusters in range(2, 8):  # Testing 2 to 7 clusters\n",
    "    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters, random_state=42)\n",
    "    labels = kmeans.fit_predict(scaled_data)\n",
    "    silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(scaled_data, labels)\n",
    "    kmeans_results.append((n_clusters, silhouette_avg))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Select the best KMeans configuration\n",
    "best_kmeans = max(kmeans_results, key=lambda x: x[1])\n",
    "best_kmeans_model = KMeans(n_clusters=best_kmeans[0], random_state=42).fit(scaled_data)\n",
    "data['KMeans_Cluster'] = best_kmeans_model.labels_\n",
    "\n",
    "# Hyperparameter tuning for DBSCAN\n",
    "dbscan_results = []\n",
    "for eps in [0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 1.0]:  # Testing different eps values\n",
    "    for min_samples in [3, 5, 10]:\n",
    "        dbscan = DBSCAN(eps=eps, min_samples=min_samples)\n",
    "        labels = dbscan.fit_predict(scaled_data)\n",
    "        # Exclude noise points (-1) from silhouette score\n",
    "        if len(set(labels)) > 1:  # Ensure at least 2 clusters\n",
    "            silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(scaled_data, labels)\n",
    "            dbscan_results.append((eps, min_samples, silhouette_avg))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Select the best DBSCAN configuration\n",
    "if dbscan_results:\n",
    "    best_dbscan = max(dbscan_results, key=lambda x: x[2])\n",
    "    best_dbscan_model = DBSCAN(eps=best_dbscan[0], min_samples=best_dbscan[1]).fit(scaled_data)\n",
    "    data['DBSCAN_Cluster'] = best_dbscan_model.labels_\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    data['DBSCAN_Cluster'] = -1  # No clusters found\n",
    "\n",
    "# Report results\n",
    "print(\"Best KMeans:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Number of Clusters: {best_kmeans[0]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Silhouette Score: {best_kmeans[1]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if dbscan_results:\n",
    "    print(\"\\nBest DBSCAN:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Eps: {best_dbscan[0]}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Min Samples: {best_dbscan[1]}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Silhouette Score: {best_dbscan[2]}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"\\nDBSCAN did not find any clusters.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save results to CSV\n",
    "data.to_csv('tuned_clustered_data.csv', index=False)\n"
   ]
  },

    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import AgglomerativeClustering\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reduce dimensions for visualization\n",
    "pca = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
    "pca_data = pca.fit_transform(scaled_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize KMeans clusters\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "plt.scatter(pca_data[:, 0], pca_data[:, 1], c=data['KMeans_Cluster'], cmap='viridis', s=50)\n",
    "plt.title('KMeans Clustering')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('PCA Component 1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('PCA Component 2')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Try Agglomerative Clustering\n",
    "agglo = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=2)\n",
    "agglo_labels = agglo.fit_predict(scaled_data)\n",
    "data['Agglomerative_Cluster'] = agglo_labels\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize Agglomerative Clustering\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
    "plt.scatter(pca_data[:, 0], pca_data[:, 1], c=agglo_labels, cmap='viridis', s=50)\n",
    "plt.title('Agglomerative Clustering')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('PCA Component 1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('PCA Component 2')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
